falling for a stupid trick--

00:11:54.631 --> 00:11:56.592 align:middle
Listen! I'm dead serious!

00:11:56.675 --> 00:11:59.636 align:middle
I've been bottling up these
feelings since we were kids!

00:11:59.720 --> 00:12:01.597 align:middle
You-- You can't be...

00:12:01.680 --> 00:12:03.682 align:middle
[HIRO]
I-It's working!

00:12:03.765 --> 00:12:06.185 align:middle
This is a master class!
You go, Hiro!

00:12:06.268 --> 00:12:08.145 align:middle
Nothing discombobulates
a potential killer

00:12:08.228 --> 00:12:10.522 align:middle
like confessing your love
for them out of nowhere!

00:12:10.606 --> 00:12:13.942 align:middle
So, you're saying that you've
harbored feelings for me

00:12:14.026 --> 00:12:15.777 align:middle
all these years?

00:12:15.861 --> 00:12:17.988 align:middle
No! You manipulative bastard!

00:12:18.071 --> 00:12:19.531 align:middle
Listen to me!

00:12:19.615 --> 00:12:21.825 align:middle
You're so much a part of my
life that I don't even know--

00:12:21.909 --> 00:12:24.119 align:middle
I don't know if I could
go on without you!

00:12:24.203 --> 00:12:26.288 align:middle
You-- You're my
everything, Alicia!

00:12:26.371 --> 00:12:27.623 align:middle
[gasping]

00:12:27.706 --> 00:12:30.375 align:middle
I want us to grow old together!
To have a family!

00:12:30.459 --> 00:12:33.795 align:middle
Make me the happiest man alive
and let me have your babies!

00:12:33.879 --> 00:12:35.756 align:middle
[ALICIA gasping]

00:12:37.549 --> 00:12:40.469 align:middle
[ALICIA]
I... I don't understand.

00:12:40.552 --> 00:12:45.057 align:middle
Was that a marriage proposal?
Is this really happening?

00:12:45.140 --> 00:12:47.809 align:middle
[HIRO]
Sweet, almost there.

00:12:47.893 --> 00:12:50.187 align:middle
Alicia! Stop this madness!

00:12:50.270 --> 00:12:53.649 align:middle
Let's put things back
the way they were!

00:12:53.732 --> 00:12:55.067 align:middle
It's too late.

00:12:55.150 --> 00:12:56.652 align:middle
Huh?

00:12:56.735 --> 00:12:58.987 align:middle
[ALICIA]
Too late, too late, too late!

00:12:59.071 --> 00:13:02.407 align:middle
We've passed
the point of no return!

00:13:02.491 --> 00:13:04.868 align:middle
I loved you with
all my heart and soul!

00:13:04.952 --> 00:13:06.495 align:middle
You were my whole world!

00:13:06.578 --> 00:13:10.249 align:middle
Martin felt the same. And yet...

00:13:10.332 --> 00:13:12.251 align:middle
You butchered him!

00:13:12.334 --> 00:13:16.004 align:middle
Um, actually, that's a strong
word, plus it was accident.

00:13:16.088 --> 00:13:17.714 align:middle
[ALICIA]
Stop saying that!

00:13:17.798 --> 00:13:20.634 align:middle
Maybe you didn't mean to kill
him but you might as well

00:13:20.717 --> 00:13:22.886 align:middle
have run him through
like a wild boar.

00:13:22.970 --> 00:13:25.138 align:middle
You wanted to leave the city!

00:13:25.222 --> 00:13:26.765 align:middle
[HIRO gasping]

00:13:26.849 --> 00:13:28.725 align:middle
[ALICIA]
Oh! You remember that now?

00:13:28.809 --> 00:13:32.229 align:middle
Your selfishness ruined our
lives in one fell swoop!

00:13:32.312 --> 00:13:34.815 align:middle
I-- I was only trying to...

00:13:34.898 --> 00:13:37.359 align:middle
[ALICIA]
Someone died! Don't you get it?

00:13:37.442 --> 00:13:40.279 align:middle
No, not just "someone."
My brother.

00:13:40.362 --> 00:13:42.990 align:middle
And why? What was the point?

00:13:43.073 --> 00:13:46.535 align:middle
It made no sense!

00:13:46.618 --> 00:13:48.871 align:middle
Then you ran and
left me here all alone.

00:13:48.954 --> 00:13:49.955 align:middle
[HIRO gasps]

00:13:50.038 --> 00:13:51.582 align:middle
[ALICIA cries]

00:13:57.546 --> 00:13:59.006 align:middle
That was awesome!

00:13:59.089 --> 00:14:02.759 align:middle
Way to play on the emotions
to keep from getting whacked!

00:14:02.843 --> 00:14:04.386 align:middle
Yeah. Awesome.

00:14:04.469 --> 00:14:06.722 align:middle
You don't sound pleased.

00:14:06.805 --> 00:14:08.724 align:middle
No? Imagine that.

00:14:08.807 --> 00:14:11.018 align:middle
I just realized
what a jerk I am.

00:14:11.101 --> 00:14:12.728 align:middle
Don't be like that.

00:14:12.811 --> 00:14:14.229 align:middle
This whole time I've
just been thinking of

00:14:14.313 --> 00:14:16.398 align:middle
everything as part of some game.

00:14:16.481 --> 00:14:18.734 align:middle
I never saw Alicia
as an old friend.

00:14:18.817 --> 00:14:21.653 align:middle
And Martin was just some guy.

00:14:22.988 --> 00:14:25.032 align:middle
But I've been a big
part of their lives.

00:14:25.115 --> 00:14:28.702 align:middle
To them, we've known each other
forever. We're like a family.

00:14:28.785 --> 00:14:31.538 align:middle
And I'm pretty sure
Alicia was in love.

00:14:31.622 --> 00:14:34.333 align:middle
My actions cost Martin his life.

00:14:34.416 --> 00:14:37.544 align:middle
Then I ran away.
I could've stayed.

00:14:37.628 --> 00:14:40.005 align:middle
I could've tried to
help him, but no.

00:14:40.088 --> 00:14:43.217 align:middle
I took off like a coward.

00:14:43.300 --> 00:14:48.180 align:middle
Out of everything I've done,
that's the absolute worst.

00:14:48.263 --> 00:14:52.392 align:middle
Oh, man. I suck. Not like
that's news, though.

00:14:52.476 --> 00:14:55.646 align:middle
[REONA] U-Uh. Okay, before
you get too down on yourself,

00:14:55.729 --> 00:14:58.106 align:middle
bear in mind,
they're all just NPCs.

00:14:58.190 --> 00:15:00.776 align:middle
[MIZARISA grunts]

00:15:00.859 --> 00:15:02.986 align:middle
Well, that's the first
time I've met someone

00:15:03.070 --> 00:15:04.947 align:middle
who could take me
out in two hits.

00:15:05.030 --> 00:15:06.907 align:middle
Thank you. You all right?

00:15:06.990 --> 00:15:08.200 align:middle
[MIZARISA]
No worries.

00:15:08.283 --> 00:15:12.162 align:middle
And please, don't
thank me. Unless...

00:15:12.246 --> 00:15:14.706 align:middle
You wanna gimme your
pinky finger as a keepsake.

00:15:14.790 --> 00:15:18.085 align:middle
[HIRO] Um, no. Matter of fact,
you should leave.

00:15:18.168 --> 00:15:20.420 align:middle
[MIZARISA]
Aw!

00:15:28.262 --> 00:15:33.141 align:middle
[REONA] We'll need to
take it to a blacksmith.

00:15:33.225 --> 00:15:34.768 align:middle
Or, better idea...

00:15:34.852 --> 00:15:36.812 align:middle
Where can I find
the Kenura tree?

00:15:36.895 --> 00:15:37.771 align:middle
[REONA]
Huh?

00:15:37.855 --> 00:15:39.857 align:middle
You know what I mean.

00:15:39.940 --> 00:15:42.693 align:middle
Big tree, tiny hill.
Yeah. It's not far.

00:15:42.776 --> 00:15:45.445 align:middle
Just a bit south
of here, actually.

00:15:45.529 --> 00:15:48.198 align:middle
Wait for me. I'll be back.

00:15:48.282 --> 00:15:53.370 align:middle
[REONA] Okay, but before you go,
shouldn't you pee?

00:15:53.453 --> 00:15:57.040 align:middle
I'll be fine. Let me do this.

00:16:14.600 --> 00:16:19.396 align:middle
Martin. You're here, right?
Come on out.

00:16:29.656 --> 00:16:32.451 align:middle
[MARTIN]
Hiro...

00:16:32.534 --> 00:16:35.412 align:middle
[HIRO]
Oh, hey. How's it going?

00:16:35.495 --> 00:16:38.498 align:middle
Strange. I thought
you'd be frightened.

00:16:38.582 --> 00:16:41.460 align:middle
I guess I'm just used
to it by now, y'know?

00:16:41.543 --> 00:16:44.171 align:middle
Have you come to join
me in the hereafter?

00:16:44.254 --> 00:16:46.840 align:middle
'Fraid I have to
disappoint you, old pal.

00:16:46.924 --> 00:16:51.428 align:middle
But, uh, there's something
I really wanted to say.

00:16:51.512 --> 00:16:53.889 align:middle
[HIRO] Except wanting to
and being able to

00:16:53.972 --> 00:16:59.853 align:middle
are two different things. I
don't have the words for this.

00:16:59.937 --> 00:17:03.482 align:middle
[HIRO]
Dammit. Come on!

00:17:03.565 --> 00:17:06.860 align:middle
Quit being a useless
turd and think!

00:17:06.944 --> 00:17:10.489 align:middle
What would Kamui say right now?

00:17:10.572 --> 00:17:13.200 align:middle
[KAMUI] I literally spelled it
out for you in the walkthrough.

00:17:13.283 --> 00:17:15.536 align:middle
You brain-dead jackalope.

00:17:15.619 --> 00:17:16.912 align:middle
[HIRO gasps]

00:17:16.995 --> 00:17:18.247 align:middle
[HIRO]
Of course!

00:17:18.330 --> 00:17:20.832 align:middle
I was too hyper focused on
his attitude to register

00:17:20.916 --> 00:17:29.424 align:middle
what he meant. He was
trying to give me advice.

00:17:29.508 --> 00:17:35.722 align:middle
I don't expect you to forgive.
Or forget. Just come with me.

00:17:40.561 --> 00:17:44.439 align:middle
Please, Martin. Join my party.

00:17:46.483 --> 00:17:50.279 align:middle
[groaning]

00:17:58.579 --> 00:17:59.997 align:middle
Martin! Help!

00:18:00.080 --> 00:18:02.583 align:middle
Hiro won't stop chasing me!

00:18:02.666 --> 00:18:03.834 align:middle
Give her a rest.

00:18:03.917 --> 00:18:06.295 align:middle
One of these days
she's gonna get you back.

00:18:06.378 --> 00:18:08.130 align:middle
[HIRO]
Huh?

00:18:08.213 --> 00:18:10.674 align:middle
[laughs] I apologize!

00:18:10.757 --> 00:18:13.218 align:middle
Sometimes I just get
real carried away!

00:18:13.302 --> 00:18:15.929 align:middle
[laughing]

00:18:16.013 --> 00:18:18.015 align:middle
Okay, was it strictly
necessary to make

00:18:18.098 --> 00:18:19.766 align:middle
the younger version
of me sound like that?

00:18:19.850 --> 00:18:21.643 align:middle
[ALICIA]
You're not being mean enough!

00:18:21.727 --> 00:18:23.061 align:middle
You have to get mad at him!

00:18:23.145 --> 00:18:26.732 align:middle
[MARTIN] Settle down, Alicia.
He said he was sorry.

00:18:26.815 --> 00:18:29.401 align:middle
Yeah! And besides,
I was just playing!

00:18:29.484 --> 00:18:31.570 align:middle
Whatever. I swear, Martin.

00:18:31.653 --> 00:18:34.198 align:middle
You let Hiro get away
with everything.

00:18:34.281 --> 00:18:35.407 align:middle
Oh, come on.

00:18:35.490 --> 00:18:37.659 align:middle
What do you want me
to do? We're friends.

00:18:37.743 --> 00:18:40.412 align:middle
Nuh-uh! We're way
more than friends!

00:18:40.495 --> 00:18:43.123 align:middle
Me and Martin are
bestest buddies!

00:18:43.207 --> 00:18:46.251 align:middle
Yeah we are! The bestest
buddies that ever were!

00:18:46.335 --> 00:18:50.380 align:middle
Forever and ever!
Nothing will ever separate us!

00:18:50.464 --> 00:18:53.050 align:middle
[MARTIN] That's right!
Absolutely nothing!

00:18:53.133 --> 00:18:57.095 align:middle
[HIRO]
Yeah! Hiro and Martin!

00:19:24.456 --> 00:19:27.125 align:middle
Hiro and Martin.

00:19:27.209 --> 00:19:31.463 align:middle
The two bestest buddies
that ever were.

00:19:31.547 --> 00:19:33.340 align:middle
Well, what do you know?

00:19:33.423 --> 00:19:36.426 align:middle
You do remember the
words of our promise.

00:19:38.595 --> 00:19:43.183 align:middle
[gasps] What? I don't get it.
What's going on?

00:19:43.267 --> 00:19:44.476 align:middle
Farewell.

00:19:44.560 --> 00:19:45.727 align:middle
You can't go!

00:19:45.811 --> 00:19:48.856 align:middle
I asked you to become
a member of my party!

00:19:48.939 --> 00:19:51.817 align:middle
I know you did, old friend.
And I'm grateful.

00:19:51.900 --> 00:19:54.152 align:middle
Okay, then. So come with me!

00:19:54.236 --> 00:19:56.572 align:middle
[MARTIN laughs]
I have to move on now.

00:19:56.655 --> 00:19:58.365 align:middle
Martin Time is over.

00:19:58.448 --> 00:20:00.826 align:middle
[HIRO gasps]

00:20:00.909 --> 00:20:04.454 align:middle
By the way. Thank you, Hiro.

00:20:21.805 --> 00:20:23.265 align:middle
[REONA]
Hey.

00:20:23.348 --> 00:20:25.934 align:middle
What are you doing?
Were you watching us?

00:20:26.018 --> 00:20:28.270 align:middle
[REONA]
Yeah. Sorry.

00:20:28.353 --> 00:20:32.274 align:middle
[HIRO]
Eh. No worries. We're good.

00:20:35.527 --> 00:20:40.324 align:middle
Martin. Oh, man.
Why'd you have to...?

00:20:40.407 --> 00:20:42.409 align:middle
Hope I didn't ruin the
moment or anything,

00:20:42.492 --> 00:20:44.912 align:middle
but for what it's worth,
I could only see you.

00:20:44.995 --> 00:20:47.080 align:middle
So, there's that at least.

00:20:47.164 --> 00:20:50.375 align:middle
Even if... you kinda looked
like a crazy person

00:20:50.459 --> 00:20:52.419 align:middle
hashing it out with
the voices in his head.

00:20:52.503 --> 00:20:54.922 align:middle
[HIRO]
Is that supposed to comfort me?

00:20:55.005 --> 00:20:57.925 align:middle
Huh...? Never mind that!
Look at your nameplate!

00:20:58.008 --> 00:21:01.929 align:middle
[HIRO]
Never mind the fact you just--

00:21:02.012 --> 00:21:06.058 align:middle
"Best Best Friend Killer:
The Best Amicide"?

00:21:07.476 --> 00:21:09.895 align:middle
Um, yeah. That wording's
a little awkward.

00:21:09.978 --> 00:21:11.939 align:middle
Turn that frown upside down!

00:21:12.022 --> 00:21:14.858 align:middle
You've got a snazzy new title.
Plus, you're no longer

00:21:14.942 --> 00:21:16.985 align:middle
being haunted
by a vengeful spirit!

00:21:17.069 --> 00:21:19.279 align:middle
I think we can count
those as positives!

00:21:19.363 --> 00:21:22.324 align:middle
Sure, but there's still
Alicia to worry about.

00:21:22.407 --> 00:21:25.410 align:middle
And you'll handle that better
the next time around, yeah?

00:21:25.494 --> 00:21:28.372 align:middle
Come on, kiddo!
You're making progress!

00:21:28.455 --> 00:21:30.374 align:middle
You're not just saying that,
are you?

00:21:30.457 --> 00:21:32.709 align:middle
No! Now buck up!

00:21:32.793 --> 00:21:35.379 align:middle
Let's get that sword
to a blacksmith ASAP.

00:21:35.462 --> 00:21:38.215 align:middle
Oh, and uh... while we're at it,
we can buy you some new pants.

00:21:38.298 --> 00:21:40.217 align:middle
Right! I still smell like pee!

00:21:40.300 --> 00:21:42.094 align:middle
[REONA laughs]
You're adorable!

00:21:42.177 --> 00:21:43.679 align:middle
[BOTH laughing]

00:21:43.762 --> 00:21:45.472 align:middle
[bell ringing]

00:21:45.556 --> 00:21:46.557 align:middle
[BOTH gasp]

00:21:46.640 --> 00:21:47.599 align:middle
Am I losing my mind

00:21:47.683 --> 00:21:50.143 align:middle
or is that the sound
of church bells?

00:21:50.227 --> 00:21:51.019 align:middle
[HIRO gasping]

00:21:51.103 --> 00:21:53.480 align:middle
[REONA]
That can't be good!

00:21:54.690 --> 00:21:56.108 align:middle
[gasps]

00:21:56.191 --> 00:22:00.696 align:middle
[ringing continues]

00:22:02.239 --> 00:22:04.283 align:middle
[HIRO]
Mind telling me what's going on?

00:22:04.366 --> 00:22:08.620 align:middle
[REONA] Um, I would, but
honestly, I have no idea.

00:22:09.997 --> 00:22:14.418 align:middle
I've never seen this...
The City of Ted is on fire!

00:23:45.759 --> 00:23:49.763 align:middle
[HIRO] Episode 7:
"Chance of Survival 0.1%"